==English==
===Etymology===
German ''adal'' (noble) + ''berht'' (bright); Old English ''Aepelbeorht''. Became very popular in 19th century England due to Queen Victoria's consort Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha
===Proper noun===
